criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with deep infiltration endometriosis and endometrioma diagnosed through
             bimanual gynecologic examination, gynecologic ultrasound or through laparoscopically
             confirmed endometrioma and DIE together;

          -  DIE with bowel involvement that required shaving or segmental resection for colorectal
             lesions and nodules;

          -  Who completed the VAS score and BSGE questionnaire;

          -  Follow-up period of at least 3 months;

          -  Patients resistant to medical therapy (NSAIDs, OCPs, levonorgestrel-releasing
             intrauterine device (IUD), and progesterone) or refuse to use medical therapy.

        Exclusion Criteria:

        *Any other endometriosis patient that do no meet the inclusion criteria
